The paper deals with the problem of model checking existential logic on partially ordered sets, which is a topic in logic and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses algorithmic results and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper's focus on model checking and its potential applications in artificial intelligence suggest that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
